#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn9.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga "
msgstr "1. In the Woods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 4. Sambahulasutta → sambahulāsuttaṃ (bj, pts2) | sambahulā (cārika) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn9.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Sambahulasutta "
msgstr "4. Several Mendicants Set Out Wandering "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.429, sc1
msgctxt "sn9.4:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ sambahulā bhikkhū kosalesu viharanti aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "At one time several mendicants were staying in the land of the Kosalans in a certain forest grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: vassaṃvuṭṭhā → vassaṃ vutthā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn9.4:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū vassaṃvuṭṭhā temāsaccayena cārikaṃ pakkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then after completing the three months of the rainy season residence, those mendicants set out wandering. "

msgctxt "sn9.4:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā te bhikkhū apassantī paridevamānā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Not seeing those mendicants, the deity haunting that forest cried. And on that occasion they recited this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn9.4:2.1"
msgid "“Arati viya mejja khāyati, "
msgstr "“Seeing so many vacated seats today, "

# NOTE: BB’s note explains what he thinks the sense of this couplet is; but his translation doesn’t express that, at least to me.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:2.2"
msgid "Bahuke disvāna vivitte āsane; "
msgstr "it seems to me that they must have become dissatisfied. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:2.3"
msgid "Te cittakathā bahussutā, "
msgstr "They were so learned, such brilliant speakers! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:2.4"
msgid "Kome gotamasāvakā gatā”ti. "
msgstr "Where have these disciples of Gotama gone?” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn9.4:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññatarā devatā taṃ devataṃ gāthāya paccabhāsi: "
msgstr "When they had spoken, another deity replied with this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn9.4:4.1"
msgid "“Māgadhaṃ gatā kosalaṃ gatā, "
msgstr "“They’ve gone to Magadha, they’ve gone to Kosala, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:4.2"
msgid "Ekacciyā pana vajjibhūmiyā; "
msgstr "and some are in the Vajjian lands. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:4.3"
msgid "Magā viya asaṅgacārino, "
msgstr "Like deer that wander free of ties, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.4:4.4"
msgid "Aniketā viharanti bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "the mendicants live with no abode.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
